1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:46,672
CHAPTER 34:
I'M THEIR HOMEROOM TEACHER

2
00:00:47,757 --> 00:00:50,259
So the US, huh? I bet you're thrilled.

3
00:00:50,342 --> 00:00:54,555
Then again, a lot of colleges
wanted you to join them, right?

4
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:59,351
Then, are you going somewhere
like Harvard or MIT to conduct research

5
00:00:59,435 --> 00:01:01,604
or are you going there to teach?

6
00:01:04,648 --> 00:01:06,942
How long would you be away?

7
00:01:07,026 --> 00:01:08,611
A semester? A year?

8
00:01:09,487 --> 00:01:11,238
I guess what I'm asking…

9
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:12,948
What I want to know is…

10
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,620
If you're going away for a long time,

11
00:01:18,662 --> 00:01:22,666
does that mean
I won't see you in my senior year?

12
00:01:30,966 --> 00:01:32,843
It's late. Go home.

13
00:01:37,014 --> 00:01:38,098
Get home safely, Eui-ju.

14
00:01:48,275 --> 00:01:50,486
So, when are you leaving?

15
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:00,996
About that proposal
from your friend Deul-i.

16
00:02:01,664 --> 00:02:02,790
What do you think?

17
00:02:05,084 --> 00:02:07,169
So seize this opportunity
and go to the US.

18
00:02:07,253 --> 00:02:08,420
Go do the research you want to do.

19
00:02:14,927 --> 00:02:15,761
Still,

20
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,556
does he have to go with her?

21
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,308
So,

22
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:24,186
is she his girlfriend after all?

23
00:02:27,398 --> 00:02:28,732
Well,

24
00:02:28,816 --> 00:02:31,777
he's a person just like the rest of us.
Of course, he's gonna date.

25
00:02:35,531 --> 00:02:37,449
They'll do research together

26
00:02:38,409 --> 00:02:39,952
in the US.

27
00:02:40,703 --> 00:02:41,829
Just the two of them.

28
00:02:43,998 --> 00:02:44,999
Good for them.

29
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,255
Hang on.

30
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:53,173
If I hadn't overheard them earlier,

31
00:02:53,257 --> 00:02:55,009
when was he planning on telling me?

32
00:02:56,218 --> 00:02:57,344
At the end of the year?

33
00:02:57,428 --> 00:02:59,722
Like, "Bye, kids. I'm off to the US."

34
00:03:04,768 --> 00:03:05,769
No.

35
00:03:07,146 --> 00:03:09,106
Why would he bother saying anything?

36
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:13,485
It's his life after all.

37
00:03:15,029 --> 00:03:17,448
I'm just one of his students.

38
00:03:28,626 --> 00:03:30,628
EPISODE 11

39
00:03:34,757 --> 00:03:38,636
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

40
00:03:43,682 --> 00:03:45,225
Is everyone here except Ji-a and Jenny?

41
00:03:45,976 --> 00:03:47,561
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

42
00:03:47,645 --> 00:03:49,563
The career experience program signup
closes this week.

43
00:03:49,647 --> 00:03:51,440
Check the notice in our group chat.

44
00:03:52,483 --> 00:03:53,609
If you're interested,

45
00:03:53,692 --> 00:03:55,694
fill out an application
and give it to Ha-su.

46
00:03:56,362 --> 00:03:57,279
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

47
00:03:57,363 --> 00:03:59,573
-Collect them and bring them to me.
-Yes, sir.

48
00:04:01,116 --> 00:04:02,117
Dismissed.

49
00:04:02,201 --> 00:04:03,869
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

50
00:04:07,623 --> 00:04:10,167
Ji-a's absent again today.
What are you going to do?

51
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,127
Won't he give you more demerits?

52
00:04:13,337 --> 00:04:14,880
Do you think something happened to her?

53
00:04:16,173 --> 00:04:17,007
Like what?

54
00:04:17,091 --> 00:04:18,801
I don't know.

55
00:04:33,399 --> 00:04:35,734
CLOUD YOUTH SHELTER

56
00:04:35,818 --> 00:04:36,902
Can I help you?

57
00:04:37,528 --> 00:04:38,445
Hello.

58
00:04:38,529 --> 00:04:41,949
I'm Yeo Eui-ju,
and I'm Ji-a's classmate at school.

59
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:45,953
Ji-a didn't come to school today,
so I was wondering if she's okay.

60
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:48,080
She's not here right now.

61
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:49,999
I think she's at her part-time job.

62
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:53,794
Do you know where she works?

63
00:04:54,420 --> 00:04:55,546
Where was it again?

64
00:04:56,922 --> 00:04:59,091
I believe it's a burger joint.

65
00:04:59,174 --> 00:05:01,093
The one at the intersection
by the Red Cross Hospital.

66
00:05:02,469 --> 00:05:03,387
I see.

67
00:05:04,054 --> 00:05:05,973
-Thank you.
-I should be thanking you

68
00:05:06,056 --> 00:05:07,349
for coming here to check on her.

69
00:05:07,975 --> 00:05:08,809
Bye.

70
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:17,776
Mr. Ga.

71
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:21,363
Ji-a isn't here right now.

72
00:05:21,447 --> 00:05:22,823
She's probably at her work.

73
00:05:24,158 --> 00:05:25,617
How come you're here?

74
00:05:27,119 --> 00:05:30,622
I saw her write this place
as her address last year.

75
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:34,209
I'll go look for her. You can go home now.

76
00:05:36,879 --> 00:05:38,088
I don't want to.

77
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:41,050
I'm fed up with cleaning
to offset my demerits.

78
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,551
I must see her myself today.

79
00:05:45,387 --> 00:05:46,388
But…

80
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:56,065
-Ji-a?
-Yes.

81
00:05:56,148 --> 00:05:57,232
She quit.

82
00:05:57,816 --> 00:05:59,526
What? When?

83
00:06:00,986 --> 00:06:01,820
Maybe two weeks ago.

84
00:06:01,904 --> 00:06:03,530
No, about three weeks ago.

85
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:07,618
Then do you know where she is right now?

86
00:06:08,619 --> 00:06:09,536
Some barbecue place.

87
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:11,872
She said they offered a better pay.

88
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:14,124
-Do you know the name?
-No, I don't.

89
00:06:14,208 --> 00:06:15,751
I didn't ask, you see.

90
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:19,463
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

91
00:06:25,677 --> 00:06:27,763
I'll go this way, you go that way.

92
00:06:27,846 --> 00:06:29,223
-Call me if you find her.
-Okay.

93
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:03,757
What the…

94
00:07:05,801 --> 00:07:06,927
Jeez.

95
00:07:07,553 --> 00:07:08,595
What's wrong with them?

96
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:11,306
Come with me.

97
00:07:12,891 --> 00:07:14,476
What do you think you're doing?

98
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,561
Are you crazy?

99
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:18,230
Hey, how can you just take drinks
from them like that?

100
00:07:18,313 --> 00:07:19,815
Do they know you're in high school?

101
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:21,733
They tip me.

102
00:07:22,317 --> 00:07:23,443
Wouldn't you drink?

103
00:07:24,862 --> 00:07:26,321
Even so…

104
00:07:26,405 --> 00:07:28,073
Ji-a?

105
00:07:29,032 --> 00:07:29,908
-Ji-a.
-Is that you?

106
00:07:29,992 --> 00:07:31,285
It's her, all right.

107
00:07:33,537 --> 00:07:36,498
Today's the day we agreed on, no?

108
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,585
I haven't been paid yet.

109
00:07:39,668 --> 00:07:40,961
-But next time--
-"Next time"?

110
00:07:42,379 --> 00:07:44,339
That's what you said last time.

111
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:46,925
Do you think we're running a charity?

112
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:51,180
We're not some philanthropists.
We have to make a living too, you know?

113
00:07:51,722 --> 00:07:53,182
I really don't have any money.

114
00:07:53,682 --> 00:07:56,393
Then do whatever it takes to get it.

115
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:57,853
Plenty of places would hire you.

116
00:07:58,437 --> 00:08:00,272
Convenience stores, coffee shops,

117
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:01,231
karaokes,

118
00:08:01,315 --> 00:08:03,066
bars.

119
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:05,903
The way I see it,

120
00:08:06,653 --> 00:08:08,614
-you could go far--
-What are you doing?

121
00:08:08,697 --> 00:08:10,407
Stop it.

122
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:11,408
Are you Ji-a's friend?

123
00:08:12,201 --> 00:08:13,452
Oh, a friend?

124
00:08:13,535 --> 00:08:16,538
We're not going to hurt her.
We're not bad guys.

125
00:08:16,622 --> 00:08:20,500
If you're that worried,
why don't you pay on her behalf?

126
00:08:21,335 --> 00:08:22,711
Do you have any money?

127
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:24,755
-That's enough.
-So?

128
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:26,131
You're scaring her.

129
00:08:26,215 --> 00:08:27,466
So then,

130
00:08:27,549 --> 00:08:29,468
how much can you give us today?

131
00:08:30,177 --> 00:08:31,762
I don't have any money.

132
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:32,804
I haven't been paid.

133
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,891
-You've got to be kidding me.
-What are you doing?

134
00:08:35,974 --> 00:08:37,142
-Let me go!
-Stop that!

135
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:38,560
You shouldn't be…

136
00:08:38,644 --> 00:08:40,062
What the heck?

137
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:42,898
-Oh, man.
-What the hell?

138
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:44,233
What do you think you're doing?

139
00:08:44,942 --> 00:08:45,901
And who might you be?

140
00:08:45,984 --> 00:08:47,778
I'm their homeroom teacher.

141
00:08:50,072 --> 00:08:52,741
-You scared me.
-Oh, their teacher?

142
00:08:53,325 --> 00:08:57,246
This is actually better.
Perhaps you can repay us on her behalf.

143
00:08:57,329 --> 00:08:59,206
You gave her this bruise, didn't you?

144
00:09:00,165 --> 00:09:01,833
We don't know anything about that.

145
00:09:02,626 --> 00:09:03,460
Sir.

146
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:07,589
She borrowed money from us, okay?

147
00:09:07,673 --> 00:09:10,467
I guess you don't teach students
to repay their debts.

148
00:09:10,968 --> 00:09:11,927
Looks like it.

149
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:16,640
How much did she borrow?

150
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,558
How much? Let's see…

151
00:09:19,226 --> 00:09:21,770
She borrowed 500,000 won.

152
00:09:21,853 --> 00:09:23,981
But with interest, it's two million won,

153
00:09:24,856 --> 00:09:25,691
sir.

154
00:09:27,651 --> 00:09:28,860
And that's all?

155
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:30,904
Mr. Ga!

156
00:09:31,655 --> 00:09:32,781
Oh, sweet.

157
00:09:32,864 --> 00:09:35,325
Dang, you're pretty cool.

158
00:09:35,409 --> 00:09:36,535
So sick.

159
00:09:36,618 --> 00:09:39,204
In that case, here.

160
00:09:39,288 --> 00:09:42,416
Wire the money to the account
at the bottom there.

161
00:09:43,792 --> 00:09:45,085
I've transferred it.

162
00:09:45,168 --> 00:09:46,378
-Oh, now?
-Did it come through?

163
00:09:46,461 --> 00:09:47,921
-Yeah.
-So it did.

164
00:09:49,339 --> 00:09:51,341
Let's make video evidence of this.

165
00:09:53,969 --> 00:09:55,804
-On November 10th,
-Yeah.

166
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:59,224
we received two million won
from Choi Ji-a.

167
00:09:59,308 --> 00:10:00,142
Indeed, we did.

168
00:10:00,225 --> 00:10:01,351
From now on,

169
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:04,146
we'll never contact her again.

170
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:06,273
-Is that okay?
-Are we done?

171
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:09,067
Delete her phone number right now.

172
00:10:09,151 --> 00:10:11,028
-Let me look up Ji-a.
-Here.

173
00:10:11,111 --> 00:10:12,779
Number deleted.

174
00:10:12,863 --> 00:10:13,947
DELETE NUMBER

175
00:10:14,031 --> 00:10:15,532
-Okay?
-Satisfied?

176
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,659
I don't want to see you ever again.

177
00:10:17,743 --> 00:10:19,578
-Yes, sir.
-You got it.

178
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:23,790
-It really was an honor to meet you.
-Totally.

179
00:10:23,874 --> 00:10:25,208
-If you ever need money,
-Oh, right.

180
00:10:25,876 --> 00:10:26,877
call us here

181
00:10:27,502 --> 00:10:29,296
-Yes.
-at the number on this business card.

182
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,840
-Call us any time.
-We'll give you a good deal.

183
00:10:32,466 --> 00:10:34,134
-Bye.
-Ji-a, we're off.

184
00:10:34,217 --> 00:10:35,052
Bye now.

185
00:10:43,310 --> 00:10:44,269
Mr. Ga.

186
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:47,356
I'll pay you back no matter what.

187
00:10:47,856 --> 00:10:50,400
It might take a while,

188
00:10:50,484 --> 00:10:51,985
but I'll make sure to pay you back.

189
00:10:53,362 --> 00:10:54,196
There's no need.

190
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:57,574
Just make sure you come to school
and try your hardest.

191
00:10:59,284 --> 00:11:01,495
-Still…
-If you really want to repay this debt,

192
00:11:02,371 --> 00:11:03,663
save it for later

193
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,625
and pay it forward if some kid needs help.

194
00:11:12,506 --> 00:11:14,049
-What are you doing?
-Huh?

195
00:11:16,218 --> 00:11:17,219
Well…

196
00:11:17,302 --> 00:11:19,596
You never know.
I'm taking a photo for evidence.

197
00:11:21,223 --> 00:11:23,475
You just love capturing
every single moment, don't you?

198
00:11:24,601 --> 00:11:25,477
Let's go.

199
00:11:28,271 --> 00:11:29,815
-Get a move on.
-Okay.

200
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:38,448
Why didn't you report it?

201
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:42,577
Another kid at the shelter
went through a similar situation.

202
00:11:43,787 --> 00:11:46,581
She got harassed
to repay the loan with steep interest.

203
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:49,584
They did report the loan sharks,

204
00:11:49,668 --> 00:11:52,003
but they came to the shelter
and caused trouble.

205
00:11:53,797 --> 00:11:55,632
That kid had to leave the shelter

206
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:57,551
for putting the other kids at risk.

207
00:12:00,262 --> 00:12:01,388
I see.

208
00:12:02,556 --> 00:12:05,600
Does this mean you can cut back
on your part-time jobs?

209
00:12:08,145 --> 00:12:08,979
No.

210
00:12:09,604 --> 00:12:10,605
I need to earn more.

211
00:12:11,815 --> 00:12:14,067
I have to leave the shelter next year.

212
00:12:14,693 --> 00:12:15,944
I'm guessing

213
00:12:16,027 --> 00:12:18,864
I'll need at least five million won
for a deposit and rent

214
00:12:18,947 --> 00:12:20,615
to get a place of my own.

215
00:12:23,702 --> 00:12:24,578
Right.

216
00:12:28,707 --> 00:12:31,084
CLOUD YOUTH SHELTER

217
00:12:37,007 --> 00:12:38,341
Thank you.

218
00:12:39,134 --> 00:12:39,968
Yeah.

219
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:42,679
Get home safe.

220
00:12:43,472 --> 00:12:45,432
Sure. See you at school.

221
00:13:00,197 --> 00:13:01,031
Let's go.

222
00:13:01,656 --> 00:13:02,574
Okay.

223
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:06,411
Ji-a was worried

224
00:13:06,495 --> 00:13:09,164
those guys would come to the shelter
and cause trouble,

225
00:13:09,247 --> 00:13:10,916
and that's why she didn't report them.

226
00:13:13,168 --> 00:13:14,294
In case she'd get kicked out.

227
00:13:16,213 --> 00:13:19,341
I never thought you'd come all this way
looking for her.

228
00:13:20,217 --> 00:13:23,345
The other teachers don't even care
if she comes to school or not.

229
00:13:25,514 --> 00:13:28,350
I doubt you came all this way
to avoid some demerits.

230
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:30,018
You're here because you were worried.

231
00:13:34,189 --> 00:13:35,273
I'm proud of you.

232
00:13:41,279 --> 00:13:43,657
Mr. Ga, if you go to the US,

233
00:13:44,282 --> 00:13:48,036
will you be doing the work you want to?

234
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:51,581
It's just…

235
00:13:52,457 --> 00:13:54,543
Just like I love writing novels,

236
00:13:54,626 --> 00:13:56,211
you might have something you like.

237
00:13:57,587 --> 00:14:02,759
Something you like so much
that you can't bear not doing it.

238
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:04,844
I wondered if that was why you were going.

239
00:14:08,557 --> 00:14:10,600
Perhaps I do have that kind of passion.

240
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:14,229
But regardless of that,
my number one priority now

241
00:14:15,063 --> 00:14:17,649
is to teach, take care of,

242
00:14:18,441 --> 00:14:19,776
and watch you guys grow.

243
00:14:21,945 --> 00:14:23,196
Nothing else matters.

244
00:15:27,177 --> 00:15:30,972
CHAPTER 35:
WE'LL HELP LIKE YOU'RE FAMILY

245
00:15:44,486 --> 00:15:45,820
Hello, what's up?

246
00:15:45,904 --> 00:15:47,072
-Hey, Jenny!
-Jenny!

247
00:15:47,155 --> 00:15:47,989
I'm back.

248
00:15:48,073 --> 00:15:49,157
-What?
-What are those?

249
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,660
It's a present for you guys.

250
00:15:51,743 --> 00:15:52,952
-Welcome back.
-Enjoy.

251
00:15:53,036 --> 00:15:54,996
-Jenny, I really missed you.
-Hi, Jenny.

252
00:16:00,001 --> 00:16:00,960
I bought these cookies

253
00:16:01,044 --> 00:16:04,464
after waiting in line
for an hour and a half in Yeonnam-dong.

254
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:06,132
-Thanks.
-Jenny got us these.

255
00:16:07,258 --> 00:16:08,218
Thanks.

256
00:16:12,514 --> 00:16:13,390
Thanks.

257
00:16:18,812 --> 00:16:19,688
What is this?

258
00:16:19,771 --> 00:16:20,939
They're so freaking good.

259
00:16:21,022 --> 00:16:22,607
-Right?
-Yeah.

260
00:16:22,691 --> 00:16:24,401
Jenny, you posted so many stories.

261
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:25,902
The updates wouldn't stop.

262
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:28,321
Yeah, you visited so many places.

263
00:16:28,405 --> 00:16:30,782
I went out early
and stayed out until late at night.

264
00:16:30,865 --> 00:16:33,118
My feet hurt so much.

265
00:16:33,201 --> 00:16:34,744
I even got blisters.

266
00:16:34,828 --> 00:16:35,662
Wanna see?

267
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:37,914
-No, thanks.
-Why would we?

268
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,874
There's really no need.

269
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:41,084
Your loss.

270
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:45,004
Come join us, Go-ya.

271
00:16:45,088 --> 00:16:46,631
I'm fine.

272
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:49,300
-What's up?
-Jenny.

273
00:16:49,384 --> 00:16:50,301
What?

274
00:16:50,885 --> 00:16:53,054
-She doesn't want to?
-Jenny.

275
00:16:53,138 --> 00:16:55,098
-You know our group chat?
-Yeah.

276
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:57,392
Can you share the list of places
you visited in Seoul?

277
00:16:57,475 --> 00:16:59,519
-Yes, please.
-The Han River and…

278
00:16:59,602 --> 00:17:00,687
Of course.

279
00:17:01,855 --> 00:17:04,774
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

280
00:17:06,317 --> 00:17:07,193
Mr. Ga!

281
00:17:07,277 --> 00:17:09,612
I'm back from Seoul.

282
00:17:10,363 --> 00:17:11,489
How was it?

283
00:17:11,573 --> 00:17:13,408
So much fun.

284
00:17:14,242 --> 00:17:15,285
Sir.

285
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:18,872
Submit your field trip report
by the end of this week.

286
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:20,457
Yes, sir.

287
00:17:27,505 --> 00:17:28,882
Time for roll call.

288
00:17:28,965 --> 00:17:29,924
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

289
00:17:35,472 --> 00:17:37,640
Okay, watch carefully.

290
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:39,893
Keep your feet shoulder-width apart.

291
00:17:40,518 --> 00:17:41,936
Then, bend your knees slightly.

292
00:17:42,854 --> 00:17:44,230
Use your weaker hand for support.

293
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:45,857
Just place it like this.

294
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:47,233
And if you just shoot…

295
00:17:48,568 --> 00:17:49,652
it won't go in.

296
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:52,947
You see that rectangle up there?

297
00:17:53,031 --> 00:17:55,200
If you aim for that when you shoot…

298
00:18:00,830 --> 00:18:02,749
You're the best!

299
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:03,708
Then, it'll go in.

300
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:06,252
Now you try.

301
00:18:07,295 --> 00:18:08,129
Ha-su.

302
00:18:16,387 --> 00:18:17,222
There you go.

303
00:18:31,694 --> 00:18:32,737
Come on, you.

304
00:18:33,780 --> 00:18:34,614
Go-ya.

305
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:37,408
No fooling around.

306
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:42,413
Hold on.

307
00:18:42,497 --> 00:18:44,082
You have to use one hand. Just one.

308
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:45,708
One hand, like this.

309
00:18:46,501 --> 00:18:50,463
Her right wrist is not in great shape.

310
00:18:51,506 --> 00:18:53,383
It gets sprained pretty easily.

311
00:18:55,093 --> 00:18:55,927
Really?

312
00:18:58,972 --> 00:19:00,348
It's fine. I can do it.

313
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,193
It's okay to sit this one out.

314
00:19:13,236 --> 00:19:15,154
Did something happen between you two?

315
00:19:16,447 --> 00:19:18,408
No. Why?

316
00:19:19,242 --> 00:19:21,202
The whole vibe is different from usual.

317
00:19:22,203 --> 00:19:23,246
You guys are not smiling.

318
00:19:24,289 --> 00:19:25,123
It's just…

319
00:19:25,915 --> 00:19:28,084
I guess we're feeling
a bit under the weather today.

320
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:36,259
Something definitely went down.

321
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:39,721
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

322
00:19:50,648 --> 00:19:52,942
What? Ji-a?

323
00:20:07,874 --> 00:20:10,293
Amazing. Turns out Ji-a's rich.

324
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:12,921
People that look like her staff
came in a car to pick her up.

325
00:20:15,506 --> 00:20:17,759
Incredible.

326
00:20:17,842 --> 00:20:18,885
I can't believe it!

327
00:20:29,771 --> 00:20:32,148
Sir! What are we going to do? It's Ji-a.

328
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:34,025
I think those guys from yesterday
grabbed her.

329
00:20:34,108 --> 00:20:35,443
-What do you mean?
-Look at this.

330
00:20:35,526 --> 00:20:37,904
Jenny saw two guys
getting her into a car and driving off.

331
00:20:37,987 --> 00:20:38,821
This is their car.

332
00:20:38,905 --> 00:20:39,948
What do we do?

333
00:20:40,031 --> 00:20:41,616
-You wait here. I'll go find her.
-Okay.

334
00:20:42,909 --> 00:20:45,036
Send me the photos of the car
and their business card.

335
00:20:45,119 --> 00:20:46,412
Yes, sir.

336
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:51,584
What do I do next?

337
00:20:52,210 --> 00:20:54,587
What else can I do? Think.

338
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:57,757
Oh, Mr. Jung.

339
00:20:58,424 --> 00:21:00,301
GOOD CONSCIENCE PAYDAY LOANS

340
00:21:12,855 --> 00:21:13,690
Have you chosen?

341
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:15,108
WE'LL HELP LIKE YOU'RE FAMILY

342
00:21:15,191 --> 00:21:16,818
If you do option C three times,

343
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:19,320
that's a million won, okay?

344
00:21:19,404 --> 00:21:20,238
Ji-a.

345
00:21:21,864 --> 00:21:23,658
-Sir!
-Sit back down.

346
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:27,036
Damn.

347
00:21:28,371 --> 00:21:30,039
I told you
I never wanted to see you again.

348
00:21:30,540 --> 00:21:32,333
Have you come all this way?

349
00:21:34,335 --> 00:21:35,503
Who's that?

350
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:39,090
He's her homeroom teacher.

351
00:21:40,758 --> 00:21:42,010
Goodness me.

352
00:21:42,719 --> 00:21:44,429
So true teachers do keep on giving.

353
00:21:47,265 --> 00:21:49,308
We're really sorry.

354
00:21:49,392 --> 00:21:51,936
The thing is,
when we did the final calculations,

355
00:21:52,562 --> 00:21:54,355
the numbers didn't add up.

356
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,941
What with inflation,

357
00:21:57,025 --> 00:21:58,401
and the way we calculate interest

358
00:21:59,444 --> 00:22:01,529
-having changed and all.
-Exactly.

359
00:22:02,113 --> 00:22:03,990
Interest used to be 20% per month,

360
00:22:04,073 --> 00:22:06,284
but we recently changed to a weekly basis.

361
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:09,620
During those few weeks
when Ji-a couldn't pay us back,

362
00:22:09,704 --> 00:22:12,373
the interest skyrocketed.

363
00:22:15,626 --> 00:22:18,463
So she still owes us
about two and a half million won.

364
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:20,048
It was paid in full the other day.

365
00:22:20,131 --> 00:22:22,467
Sir, don't listen to them.

366
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:23,718
Shut up, you!

367
00:22:24,302 --> 00:22:25,219
Don't move.

368
00:22:25,303 --> 00:22:26,429
Anyhow, sir,

369
00:22:27,055 --> 00:22:29,307
if Ji-a can't pay the money back,

370
00:22:29,390 --> 00:22:31,809
she'll have to go out to work

371
00:22:31,893 --> 00:22:34,020
at the kind of place
where pretty girls work.

372
00:22:34,645 --> 00:22:36,981
Sir, don't give them any more money.

373
00:22:37,065 --> 00:22:38,941
I'll be fine. Just hurry up and leave.

374
00:22:43,362 --> 00:22:44,322
Is there a contract?

375
00:22:45,990 --> 00:22:47,658
Let's see the contract with those terms

376
00:22:47,742 --> 00:22:49,660
drawn up on the day of the loan
if you have it.

377
00:22:51,329 --> 00:22:52,413
Huh?

378
00:22:53,247 --> 00:22:55,166
If you don't have it,
what's your basis for collecting?

379
00:23:00,463 --> 00:23:02,381
You're really starting
to get on my nerves.

380
00:23:03,966 --> 00:23:05,885
You think this is your home turf?

381
00:23:07,637 --> 00:23:09,097
Sir!

382
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:14,560
What's wrong with you? Huh?

383
00:23:17,146 --> 00:23:19,232
I see you still haven't figured me out.

384
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:24,654
Oh my!

385
00:23:40,711 --> 00:23:42,338
PAYDAY LOANS

386
00:23:48,511 --> 00:23:49,637
This must be it.

387
00:23:50,263 --> 00:23:52,515
Eui-ju, you stay here.
We'll be right back with them.

388
00:23:53,099 --> 00:23:55,101
-How can I just--
-Stay here.

389
00:23:55,184 --> 00:23:56,185
This won't take long.

390
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:16,831
Do you love jjajangmyeon that much?

391
00:24:16,914 --> 00:24:17,790
Yes, boss.

392
00:24:17,874 --> 00:24:20,251
Look at you, stuffing your face.

393
00:24:20,334 --> 00:24:21,544
Is it that good?

394
00:24:27,383 --> 00:24:28,467
Mr. Ga!

395
00:24:28,551 --> 00:24:29,677
Are you okay?

396
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:31,304
Oh, no.

397
00:24:31,387 --> 00:24:32,221
You're okay now.

398
00:24:32,305 --> 00:24:33,556
Oh, I'm sorry.

399
00:24:33,639 --> 00:24:34,724
Oh, no.

400
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:38,060
Who are these heavenly figures?

401
00:24:39,145 --> 00:24:41,063
What leads you to descend from on high

402
00:24:41,147 --> 00:24:42,815
to visit my humble place?

403
00:24:43,399 --> 00:24:44,358
Was it you bastards

404
00:24:45,818 --> 00:24:46,861
who put him in that state?

405
00:24:48,279 --> 00:24:49,113
That's right.

406
00:24:49,697 --> 00:24:51,032
This is hilarious.

407
00:24:51,115 --> 00:24:52,033
Oh, no…

408
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:09,568
Subtitle: Paul Carver
